abstract: A photograph of a Chinese woman with a bloody, newly aborted, seven-month-old fetus has led to massive outrage over the enforcement of the state's one-child policy. But many also defend the plan's original thesis, that an unchecked birth rate would threaten the country's economic gains. As the debate rages on the ground, China has sent its first female astronaut into space.

headline.main: Two Women and Two Trajectories in China
